---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const articleNavLinks = [
    { href: '#problem', label: 'The Problem' },
    { href: '#process', label: 'My Design Process' },
    { href: '#solution', label: 'The Solution' },
    { href: '#reflection', label: 'Results & Reflection' },
];
---

<Layout 
    title="BASMI Case Study"
    description="A mobile app to make dengue prevention an engaging, community-driven habit."
>
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto flex gap-8 px-4">
        <aside class="hidden md:block w-64 sticky top-24 self-start py-8">
            <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-gray-500 hover:text-gray-900 mb-8 transition-colors">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-arrow-left"><path d="m12 19-7-7 7-7"/><path d="M19 12H5"/></svg>
                <span>Back to Home</span>
            </a>
            <nav>
                <ul class="space-y-3">
                    {articleNavLinks.map(link => (
                        <li>
                            <a 
                                href={link.href} 
                                data-navlink={link.href.substring(1)}
                                class="article-nav-link text-gray-500 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
                            >
                                {link.label}
                            </a>
                        </li>
                    ))}
                </ul>
            </nav>
        </aside>

        <main class="w-full md:flex-1 font-sans text-gray-800">
            <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto pt-24 md:pt-32 pb-16 md:pb-24">
                <div class="mb-8">
                    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-gray-900">DotOS</h1>
                    <p class="mt-2 text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-500">A context-aware OS for a more personal computer</p>
                </div>

                <div class="border-t border-gray-200 pt-8">
                    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[1fr_3fr] gap-x-12 gap-y-8 mb-16">
                        <div class="space-y-8">
                            <div>
                                <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 tracking-wider uppercase">MY ROLE</h3>
                                <p class="mt-2 text-lg text-gray-800">Product Designer</p>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 tracking-wider uppercase">TEAMMATE</h3>
                                <p class="mt-2 text-lg text-gray-800">Zane Shannon</p>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 tracking-wider uppercase">TOOLS</h3>
                                <p class="mt-2 text-lg text-gray-800">Figma</p>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 tracking-wider uppercase">TIMELINE</h3>
                                <p class="mt-2 text-lg text-gray-800">2022</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="space-y-8">
                            <div>
                                <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 tracking-wider uppercase">DESCRIPTION</h3>
                                <p class="mt-2 text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">A concept for a context-aware operating system that helps you focus on what matters.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 tracking-wider uppercase">CONTEXT</h3>
                                <p class="mt-2 text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
                                    What if your computer knew what you wanted to do? Today's PC operating system know so little about us that they aren't able to help in meaningful ways. DotOS is a concept for an operating system that provides what you need, where you need it, at the times you need it the most. A rethinking of the OS for a more personal computer.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div> 

                    <div class="space-y-16">
                        <section id="problem">
                            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">The Problem</h2>
                            <div class="space-y-4 text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
                                <p>Indonesia has a national goal of "Zero Dengue Deaths by 2030," but government programs often struggle with grassroots engagement. Our research revealed that young adults in urban areas found routine prevention tedious and forgettable.</p>
                                <img src="/basmicardsticker_01.png" alt="3M sticky notes" class="rounded-xl shadow-lg my-8 w-full max-w-md mx-auto">
                                <p>Communities lacked real-time data and coordination tools. The goal was to design an intuitive and motivating mobile experience for people aged 18-35 to consistently perform dengue prevention tasks.</p>
                            </div>
                        </section>
                        <section id="process">
                            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">My Design Process</h2>
                            <div class="space-y-8 text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
                                <div>
                                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">1. User Research</h3>
                                    <p>We used a mixed-method approach, including secondary research from the WHO and Indonesian Ministry of Health, plus in-depth interviews. Key findings were inconsistency, lack of motivation, poor information flow, and limited community coordination.</p>
                                </div>
                                <div>
                                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">2. Wireframing & Iteration</h3>
                                    <p>I started with low-fidelity wireframes to establish the core layout and information architecture, allowing for rapid concept testing of the main dashboard, mission pages, and reporting forms.</p>
                                </div>
                                <div>
                                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">3. High-Fidelity Design</h3>
                                    <p>In this phase, I developed a clean and motivating visual identity. The blue and white color palette was chosen to evoke feelings of health and trust. I designed a system of cards, icons, and progress indicators to make information scannable and provide satisfying feedback.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </section>
                        <section id="solution">
                            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">The Solution</h2>
                            <div class="space-y-4 text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
                                <p>BASMI is a comprehensive platform that empowers users with the tools they need to fight dengue effectively.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="my-10 space-y-8">
                                <img src="/basmicardthumbnail.png" alt="BASMI App Interface" class="rounded-2xl shadow-2xl w-full">
                                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                                    <img src="/basmicardsticker_03.png" alt="Draining Mission Feature" class="rounded-2xl shadow-lg w-full">
                                    <img src="/basmicardsticker_04.png" alt="Covering Mission Feature" class="rounded-2xl shadow-lg w-full">
                                </div>
                                <img src="/basmicardsticker_05.png" alt="Map Feature" class="rounded-2xl shadow-lg w-full">
                            </div>
                             <div class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
                                <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">Key Features:</h3>
                                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-3">
                                    <li><strong>3M Quests:</strong> A gamified system where users complete prevention tasks to earn points and climb a community leaderboard.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Dengue-Prone Area Reporting:</strong> Allows users to photograph and geotag potential mosquito breeding grounds, creating a real-time risk map.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Heatmap:</strong> A visual map showing reported risk areas to help users and local authorities identify hotspots.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Community Events & Schedules:</strong> A centralized hub for local cleanup events and official fogging schedules.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </section>
                        <section id="reflection">
                            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Results & Reflection</h2>
                            <div class="space-y-4 text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
                                <p>We conducted two rounds of usability testing with Maze. The initial prototype scored an 80 on the System Usability Scale (SUS). After iterating on the design, the revised prototype achieved an SUS score of 88, falling into the "Excellent" category.</p>
                                <p>This project reinforced the importance of understanding user psychology. The problem wasn't a lack of information, but a lack of motivation. By applying gamification and social engagement, we designed a solution that empowers users to build lasting habits.</p>
                            </div>
                        </section>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </main>
    </Layout>